00:23:05,605 --> 00:23:10,083
- You don't want a clarinet, do you?
- Van Buren wants a clarinet.

237
00:23:10,170 --> 00:23:12,476
- Who's selling it?
- My brother.

238
00:23:12,606 --> 00:23:14,954
- I need new shoes.
- You need a new personality.

239
00:23:15,085 --> 00:23:19,128
- You stand behind me in the choir.
- I do? You do? Is that you?

240
00:23:19,607 --> 00:23:21,607
- You have a lot of energy.
- I do?

241
00:23:21,737 --> 00:23:24,391
Yeah. I mean, that's good.

242
00:23:24,477 --> 00:23:27,869
- My name's Jeannine Pratt.
- Nice. Hi.

243
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:31,129
- You're Conrad Jarrett, remember?
- Right.

244
00:23:32,913 --> 00:23:35,000
- Bye
- Bye-bye

245
00:23:37,131 --> 00:23:39,436
You got a lot of energy.

246
00:23:42,131 --> 00:23:43,914
Trick or treat!

247
00:23:44,044 --> 00:23:47,915
This is the scariest ghost I've ever
seen! And the tiger and the witch...

248
00:23:48,045 --> 00:23:50,957
You all look just wonderful.
Take an apple.

249
00:23:51,089 --> 00:23:53,133
There you go. Be careful.

250
00:23:53,263 --> 00:23:55,741
Thank you, Mrs. Jarrett. Bye.

251
00:23:57,264 --> 00:24:01,351
The Cabbots. Little Julie's first time.
God, she's so cute.

252
00:24:06,874 --> 00:24:09,047
Know what I've been thinking?

253
00:24:09,135 --> 00:24:13,266
That Christmas in London would be
like something out of Dickens.

254
00:24:13,352 --> 00:24:17,702
We've never done that before, right?
Christmas in London?

255
00:24:17,832 --> 00:24:20,702
Maybe we shouldn't plan
to go away right now.

256
00:24:22,095 --> 00:24:25,267
We talked about that.
We decided on that.

257
00:24:26,138 --> 00:24:30,399
I know we did, but the more I talk
about it, the more the timing doesn't...

258
00:24:30,486 --> 00:24:34,138
Calvin, we've always
gone away at Christmas.

259
00:24:34,268 --> 00:24:39,574
I think it would be good for him too.
Isn't it time we got back to normal?

260
00:24:39,661 --> 00:24:42,618
He's just started with this doctor.

261
00:24:42,705 --> 00:24:45,183
- So he'll miss three weeks.
- Why interrupt it?

262
00:24:45,314 --> 00:24:48,140
Because I wanna get away.

263
00:24:48,270 --> 00:24:51,706
I think we all should. It's important.

264
00:24:52,532 --> 00:24:56,271
Look, if he doesn't
go through with this now,

265
00:24:56,402 --> 00:24:58,750
he might change his mind.

266
00:24:58,881 --> 00:25:04,186
If he changes his mind,
maybe it wasn't right for him to do.

267
00:25:04,274 --> 00:25:08,881
- Does he want to go to London?
- I don't think he knows what he wants.

268
00:27:16,249 --> 00:27:17,466
I'm sorry.

269
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:20,075
- Don't do that!
- I'm sorry.

270
00:27:21,727 --> 00:27:25,293
- I didn't think you were here.
- I'm sorry. I just got in.

271
00:27:25,423 --> 00:27:28,641
- I didn't play golf. It's too cold.
- How was your golf game?

272
00:27:28,728 --> 00:27:31,902
- I didn't play.
- It did get colder today.

273
00:27:32,033 --> 00:27:34,599
No, I mean, for the year it's colder.

274
00:27:34,729 --> 00:27:36,338
Yeah.

275
00:27:37,295 --> 00:27:41,077
- Weren't you swimming today?
- Uh-huh. Sorry I scared you.

276
00:27:41,207 --> 00:27:43,903
- How'd it go?
- Good. I swam well today.

277
00:27:43,991 --> 00:27:46,209
Good.

278
00:27:46,339 --> 00:27:49,210
- I could swim the 50 if my timing...
- Off.

279
00:27:49,643 --> 00:27:53,165
..if my timing got better.
I'm just a little off on my timing.

280
00:27:53,253 --> 00:27:55,775
- Well, you have to work at that.
- Yeah.

281
00:27:57,471 --> 00:27:59,776
I got 74 on a trig quiz.

282
00:28:00,818 --> 00:28:04,471
74? Gee, I was awful at trig.

283
00:28:05,645 --> 00:28:07,559
You took trig?

284
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:12,776
Wait a minute...

285
00:28:14,777 --> 00:28:16,865
Did I take trig?

286
00:28:21,083 --> 00:28:24,170
I bought you two shirts.
They're on your bed.

287
00:28:26,822 --> 00:28:29,780
- Who's gonna be there?
- The Murrays, of course,

288
00:28:29,867 --> 00:28:33,041
and the Gunthers, the Kanes
and the good old us.

289
00:28:33,780 --> 00:28:36,954
Why don't we just
go to the movies instead?

290
00:28:37,042 --> 00:28:38,999
Don't be negative.

291
00:28:39,085 --> 00:28:41,782
That's not negative.
That's unpredictable.

292
00:28:41,912 --> 00:28:44,912
- Come on. Let's really go to the movies.
- OK.

293
00:28:45,999 --> 00:28:48,522
- Really?
- OK, yeah. Let's go.

294
00:28:49,913 --> 00:28:52,173
What's our excuse?

295
00:28:53,566 --> 00:28:56,261
Beth wanted to go to the movies?

296
00:28:56,348 --> 00:28:58,869
Good. Very good.

297
00:29:04,915 --> 00:29:09,002
All right, now, smile.
And remember, not too many martinis.

298
00:29:14,524 --> 00:29:17,613
Hello, Gladyce. Will you put that
with the rest of them?

299
00:29:17,699 --> 00:29:21,917
- We're in time for the grand entrance.
- Look who's here!

300
00:29:22,483 --> 00:29:25,136
Three blocks away
and the last to arrive.

301
00:29:25,266 --> 00:29:26,701
Come on in.

302
00:29:26,787 --> 00:29:31,092
Clark! Happy birthday.
You look wonderful for a 75-year-old.

303
00:29:37,703 --> 00:29:40,180
- Hey, partner. How are you?
- Hey, pal.

304
00:29:41,398 --> 00:29:44,703
- Hi, Beth.
- And where were you at the lunch?

305
00:29:44,833 --> 00:29:48,095
- Borrow the money.
- I was thinking of going public.

306
00:29:48,183 --> 00:29:51,833
I wouldn't do that now.
Cos the market's low.

307
00:29:51,964 --> 00:29:56,226
Your hair looks wonderful.
It's shorter, isn't it? I like that.

308
00:29:56,313 --> 00:30:01,052
I said "Would you please put out
our cigar?" and he says "Huh?"

309
00:30:01,183 --> 00:30:05,010
I said "Will you put out your cigar?"
and he says "I don't have another one."

310
00:30:06,445 --> 00:30:08,489
Good to see you.

311
00:30:09,837 --> 00:30:12,401
It's a macho factor.
When these kids are at school,

312
00:30:12,532 --> 00:30:16,447
they just think they've got
to walk on the edge of danger.

313
00:30:16,577 --> 00:30:20,840
- What are these hushed tones about?
- He just told the funniest joke!

314
00:30:24,230 --> 00:30:26,796
- I'm not talking to you.
- Why?

315
00:30:27,013 --> 00:30:30,579
Obviously, you know, I have
my fingers crossed on this merger.

316
00:30:30,710 --> 00:30:32,927
- Let's get together for lunch.
- Great.

317
00:30:33,013 --> 00:30:36,406
Call me in the office.
I have no idea what my schedule is.

318
00:30:36,536 --> 00:30:39,971
I ran into Billy White.
Bob McClean's leaving Coles & Johnson.

319
00:30:40,058 --> 00:30:43,103
- Where's he going?
- He doesn't know.

320
00:30:44,581 --> 00:30:48,799
No, you didn't. You are so mean.
He's the meanest man you ever met.

321
00:30:49,712 --> 00:30:51,146
When a ball is in play,

322
00:30:51,234 --> 00:30:55,843
if a player, his partner, their equipment
or their caddies accidentally move it...

323
00:31:19,368 --> 00:31:20,847
Hi, Annie.

324
00:31:20,934 --> 00:31:24,891
- What's your boy up to these days?
- Who knows? They won't tell.

325
00:31:24,978 --> 00:31:28,500
- How's Conrad doing?
- He's great. Just great.

326
00:31:29,543 --> 00:31:32,544
I asked Donald and he says
they haven't talked much.

327
00:31:32,674 --> 00:31:35,719
I said "Maybe he's
a little self-conscious."

328
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:42,197
No, no.

329
00:31:43,328 --> 00:31:44,850
No, he's...

330
00:31:44,980 --> 00:31:48,198
There's a doctor in Highland Park
that he sees mice a week.

331
00:31:48,285 --> 00:31:50,894
That kinda cuts into his social life.

332
00:31:51,284 --> 00:31:56,417
- He's great, just great.
- Really? Is he still having problems?

333
00:31:56,504 --> 00:32:01,026
Oh, no. Nothing like that.
Just somebody to talk to, that's all.

334
00:32:01,156 --> 00:32:03,896
Polish off the rough edges, that's all.

335
00:32:04,027 --> 00:32:06,766
How you doing, darling?
Is he falling asleep yet?

336
00:32:06,853 --> 00:32:09,287
No. He's great.

337
00:32:09,419 --> 00:32:11,417
Mr. Great, that's me.

338
00:32:19,247 --> 00:32:22,116
- You drink too much at parties.
- I'm not drunk.

339
00:32:22,247 --> 00:32:25,116
Why did you say
Conrad is seeing a psychiatrist?

340
00:32:25,247 --> 00:32:26,594
Why not?

341
00:32:26,726 --> 00:32:29,857
People don't hear
that kind of thing very easily.

342
00:32:29,988 --> 00:32:33,160
for most people it's a status symbol,
like going to Europe.

343
00:32:33,248 --> 00:32:36,291
Well, I thought blurting it out
was in very bad taste.

344
00:32:36,379 --> 00:32:38,510
Not to mention a violation of privacy.

345
00:32:38,641 --> 00:32:41,684
- Whose privacy?
- Our privacy. The family's privacy.

346
00:32:41,814 --> 00:32:44,380
I think it is a very private matter.

347
00:32:53,034 --> 00:32:55,468
So what do I do? Tell you my dreams?

348
00:32:55,554 --> 00:32:57,816
I don't hold much stock in dreams.

349
00:32:57,947 --> 00:33:00,598
All psychiatrists believe in dreams.

350
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:02,687
Really?

351
00:33:02,774 --> 00:33:04,861
What's happening?

352
00:33:05,644 --> 00:33:08,165
What's going on?

353
00:33:08,295 --> 00:33:10,774
I just feel so...

354
00:33:12,861 --> 00:33:15,428
- What?
- Jumpy. I don't know...

355
00:33:16,471 --> 00:33:18,994
Look, kiddo...

356
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:22,081
I lied. I do believe in dreams.

357
00:33:22,994 --> 00:33:25,909
But I wanna know what's happening
when you're awake.

358
00:33:25,995 --> 00:33:29,560
Something's making you nervous.
You're making me nervous.

359
00:33:29,690 --> 00:33:31,778
Maybe I need a tranquillizer.

360
00:33:31,908 --> 00:33:35,082
- Tranquillizer.
- Yeah. What do you think?

361
00:33:35,692 --> 00:33:38,865
You came in looking like
something out of the Body Snatchers,

362
00:33:38,995 --> 00:33:42,474
It's not my impression
that you need a tranquillizer.

363
00:33:44,954 --> 00:33:47,258
- What is this?
- Clock.

364
00:33:48,910 --> 00:33:52,389
So you get to tell the time, but I can't?

365
00:33:52,998 --> 00:33:55,259
- So you know when the hour's up?
- Right.

366
00:33:55,389 --> 00:33:58,260
50 minutes, 55 minutes? What is it?

367
00:34:06,347 --> 00:34:09,218
Maybe I don't wanna swim any more.

368
00:34:09,348 --> 00:34:11,695
I mean, my timing's for shit.

369
00:34:11,826 --> 00:34:15,652
Now he's got mo guys swimming
the 50 that are better than me.

370
00:34:15,783 --> 00:34:18,176
Jeez, they're a bunch
of boring-ass jocks.

371
00:34:18,306 --> 00:34:21,959
And him, I can't stand him.
He's a tight-ass son of a bitch.

372
00:34:22,045 --> 00:34:23,394
Ever thought of quitting?

373
00:34:23,524 --> 00:34:26,046
- Are you telling me to?
- No.

374
00:34:26,742 --> 00:34:30,786
- It wouldn't look good.
- forget how it looks. How does it feel?

375
00:34:32,134 --> 00:34:34,264
How does it feel? How does it feel?

376
00:34:34,352 --> 00:34:37,265
Yes. How does it feel?

377
00:34:39,222 --> 00:34:42,527
It's the same damn thing I did last year.

378
00:34:42,613 --> 00:34:45,265
- Are you the same person as last year?
- I don't know.

379
00:34:45,396 --> 00:34:47,136
- So you need a tranquillizer?
- You tell me.

380
00:34:47,266 --> 00:34:48,396
It's up to you.

381
00:34:48,484 --> 00:34:51,441
$50 an hour. Can't you decide
if I should have a pill or not?

382
00:34:51,528 --> 00:34:55,224
- I'm supposed to feel better, right?
- Not necessarily.

383
00:35:01,486 --> 00:35:04,399
How is it with your friends?
Getting any easier?

384
00:35:04,529 --> 00:35:06,572
No, it's still hard.

385
00:35:06,703 --> 00:35:08,747
Is anyplace easy?

386
00:35:12,487 --> 00:35:15,618
- The hospital was.
- It was? Why?

387
00:35:17,792 --> 00:35:21,010
Because nobody hid anything there.

388
00:35:21,358 --> 00:35:23,967
Was there anyone there
you could talk to?

389
00:35:25,446 --> 00:35:27,793
I mean besides Dr. Crawford?

390
00:35:38,185 --> 00:35:39,229
Hi.

391
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:41,273
Hey, Karen.

392
00:35:41,405 --> 00:35:42,665
Hi.

393
00:35:42,796 --> 00:35:45,623
- How are you?
- Good. Real good.

394
00:35:45,709 --> 00:35:48,232
- Sit down, please.
- Thank you.

395
00:36:17,019 --> 00:36:20,019
- When did you get back?
- The end of August.

396
00:36:20,671 --> 00:36:21,714
God...

397
00:36:21,845 --> 00:36:24,063
- It's great to see you.
- You too.

398
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:29,760
I can't stay a real long time.
I've got a meeting over at school.

399
00:36:29,890 --> 00:36:33,802
Drama club meeting. We're doing
A thousand Crowns this year.

400
00:36:33,933 --> 00:36:38,543
We are going crazy trying to get it
together. I'm secretary this year too.

401
00:36:38,629 --> 00:36:41,109
- Don't let me hang you up.
- You're not.

402
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:43,716
No, I really wanted to see you.

403
00:36:44,716 --> 00:36:49,153
I didn't know quite what to expect.
You sounded sorta funny on the phone.

404
00:36:49,283 --> 00:36:53,675
No, I wasn't... It was a gray day,
that's all. Kind of...

405
00:36:53,763 --> 00:36:56,763
But everything's great.
I'm in school, on the swim team.

406
00:36:56,849 --> 00:37:01,285
You're swimming. Terrific, Conrad.
God, that's really wonderful.

407
00:37:01,415 --> 00:37:04,329
We haven't had any meets yet.
I could stay on the bench...

408
00:37:04,459 --> 00:37:06,762
Come on, you'll do great.

409
00:37:07,024 --> 00:37:10,198
- I bet your folks are real proud of you.
- Yeah.

410
00:37:12,633 --> 00:37:15,416
- What can I get you guys?
- Are you hungry at all?

411
00:37:15,548 --> 00:37:19,070
- I just want a Coke.
- Two Cokes, please.

412
00:37:20,809 --> 00:37:23,984
- You think we offended him?
- Something I said?

413
00:37:25,507 --> 00:37:28,071
Definitely a low self-image day.

414
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:31,376
So.

415
00:37:31,463 --> 00:37:33,550
- Are you...
- What are...

416
00:37:36,029 --> 00:37:40,637
I can't believe how beautiful you look.
You really look beautiful.

417
00:37:41,550 --> 00:37:43,421
So do you.

418
00:37:43,551 --> 00:37:45,900
- Do you miss it?
- Miss what?

419
00:37:46,030 --> 00:37:48,377
- The hospital.
- No.

420
00:37:49,856 --> 00:37:50,899
Thank you.

421
00:37:51,031 --> 00:37:53,987
- You don't miss it? Nothing about it?
- No.

422
00:37:54,118 --> 00:37:56,684
You don't miss Leo's corny jokes?

423
00:38:01,249 --> 00:38:05,467
- Are you seeing a doctor?
- Yeah, I'm seeing a doctor. Are you?

424
00:38:08,033 --> 00:38:11,599
Well, Dr. Crawford gave me a name,
and I went for a while, but...

425
00:38:12,380 --> 00:38:16,991
It just didn't work for me, I guess.
He kept telling me what I already knew,

426
00:38:17,122 --> 00:38:21,339
and finally I decided the only one
who can help me is myself.

427
00:38:23,904 --> 00:38:26,557
At least, that's what my dad says.

428
00:38:27,644 --> 00:38:30,255
I don't mean it's not right
for you, Conrad.

429
00:38:30,385 --> 00:38:33,123
If it's what you wanna do,
that's what you should do.

430
00:38:33,253 --> 00:38:37,603
I don't know how long I'm gonna
keep it up. I sorta got shoved into it.

431
00:38:40,124 --> 00:38:42,211
Your hair grew in.

432
00:38:42,820 --> 00:38:45,472
That was such a dumb thing to do.

433
00:38:47,343 --> 00:38:49,647
- I like it.
- You do?

434
00:38:53,604 --> 00:38:55,822
I don't know, I just...

435
00:38:55,909 --> 00:38:58,561
I miss it sometimes, the hospital.

436
00:38:59,431 --> 00:39:01,518
Really do.

437
00:39:03,084 --> 00:39:07,780
- Things have to change, you know.
- But that's where we had the laughs.

438
00:39:07,910 --> 00:39:10,693
But that was a hospital.

439
00:39:10,823 --> 00:39:12,911
This is the real world.

440
00:39:13,042 --> 00:39:15,173
Yeah. I guess you're right.

441
00:39:22,696 --> 00:39:25,479
I really have to go.

442
00:39:25,566 --> 00:39:29,827
I'm sorry. I have a meeting
over at the school.

443
00:39:29,957 --> 00:39:32,305
Drama club meeting. We're doing
A thousand Crowns...

444
00:39:32,436 --> 00:39:34,697
I know. You told me.

445
00:39:36,698 --> 00:39:39,088
- Did I?
- Yeah.

446
00:39:40,915 --> 00:39:43,828
I better hurry. Don't wanna be late.

447
00:39:47,482 --> 00:39:50,524
Thanks for seeing me.

448
00:39:51,177 --> 00:39:53,656
Conrad?

449
00:39:53,786 --> 00:39:56,265
Let's have a great Christmas.

450
00:39:59,004 --> 00:40:00,874
OK?

451
00:40:01,004 --> 00:40:04,005
Let's have a great year.

452
00:40:05,832 --> 00:40:09,398
Let's have the best year
of our whole lives, OK?

453
00:40:09,528 --> 00:40:12,788
We can, you know.
This could be the best year ever.

454
00:40:13,440 --> 00:40:15,659
Yeah.

455
00:40:17,225 --> 00:40:19,269
Yeah.

456
00:40:21,747 --> 00:40:23,400
- Will you call me?
- Yeah.

457
00:40:23,487 --> 00:40:25,574
- You mean it?
- Yep.

458
00:40:28,270 --> 00:40:31,574
You... you look good, Conrad.

459
00:40:34,271 --> 00:40:36,358
Bye, Bye
- b Y e.

460
00:40:42,402 --> 00:40:44,488
Would you cheer up?

461
00:41:23,842 --> 00:41:26,278
It's cold out here.

462
00:41:27,756 --> 00:41:31,018
You should put that on,
or do you want a sweater?

463
00:41:31,713 --> 00:41:33,802
Do I need one?

464
00:41:39,279 --> 00:41:41,758
- What are you doin'?
- Nothin'.

465
00:41:43,193 --> 00:41:45,149
Thinkin'.

466
00:41:46,411 --> 00:41:49,715
- About what?
- Not about anything.

467
00:41:52,759 --> 00:41:56,238
Your hair is starting to grow out.

468
00:41:56,326 --> 00:41:58,760
It's looking better.

469
00:42:05,195 --> 00:42:07,239
I was thinking about the pigeon.

470
00:42:07,326 --> 00:42:09,892
The one that used to
hang around the garage.

471
00:42:10,022 --> 00:42:14,718
He'd get on top of your car and take off
when you pulled out of the driveway.

472
00:42:14,848 --> 00:42:17,024
Yeah, I remember.

473
00:42:18,155 --> 00:42:23,546
I remember how scared I used to get,
that whoosh...

